This paper discusses the implementation of GNU Prolog, which is a programming language and falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the system organization, performance, and portability issues, which are related to Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the finite domain constraint solver, which is a topic in Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the position of GNU Prolog with respect to other Prolog system implementations, which is a topic in Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
